gap-C diagnosis (the deeper bug surfaced, honest @D g3):
  PTX L78:  `shfl.sync.bfly.b32 %r18, %r9, %r16, 0x1f, 0xffffffff;`
            % r9 and %r16 are referenced but NEVER declared in the .reg
            section. ptxas: "Unknown symbol '%r9' / '%r16'".

  Source MIR call:  gpu_warp_shuffle_xor(sum, mask)
    `sum`  is FP64 (let mut sum: f64 = 0.0) — classifier puts it in
           %fd<id> bank (visible as %fd9 at L53, declared L19).
    `mask` is i32  (let mut mask: i32 = 16) — classifier puts it in
           %r<id> bank with id=16 BUT no `.reg .u32 %r16;` declaration is
           emitted by the kind table; only %r18/%r19 get declarations.

  Codegen path (compiler/codegen/nvptx_target.hexa _nvptx_lower_stmt
                gpu_warp_shuffle_xor arm, restored in commit 7671d7db):

      let src_reg  = _nvptx_reg_u32(s.args[0].local_id)   // → "%r" + id
      let mask_reg = _nvptx_reg_u32(s.args[1].local_id)   // → "%r" + id

  Both operands are formatted as `%r<local_id>` regardless of actual bank.
  FP64-typed arg[0] (`sum`) is FP64-banked as `%fd9` — but this emit
  writes `%r9`, picking a slot in the u32 bank that was never declared.

  Per the fixture comment L22-25 (intentional design note):
      gpu_warp_shuffle_xor(v, mask) [NOT WIRED — XOR butterfly variant
      of existing gpu_warp_shuffle(v, lane) idx-mode; FP64-shuffle would
      compose from 2× u32 halves per PTX ISA §9.7.13.4]

  The author KNEW FP64-shuffle requires composition: split FP64 into hi/lo
  u32 halves via `mov.b64 {%r_lo, %r_hi}, %fd_src;`, shfl each half
  separately, then `mov.b64 %fd_dst, {%r_lo, %r_hi};`. The N71-A wiring
  closed the call-site → PTX-mnemonic gap (shfl.sync.bfly.b32 IS now
  emitted) but did NOT add the FP64 decomposition wrapper.

  Closure path (NEXT cycle, out of N91 scope):
    Option A — kernel rewrite: change `sum` to i64-bitcast or do the
               manual hi/lo split in source. Cheap, kernel-specific.
    Option B — codegen extension: detect FP64 first arg to
               gpu_warp_shuffle_xor and synthesize 2× u32 halves +
               2× shfl + recompose. Reusable; matches gpu/SPEC.md §5.

  Both options touch compiler-or-fixture source; deferred from this
  re-fire workflow.


